description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an energetic and flexible registered Nurse(s) to join our well established team on the Elective Orthopaedic/Neurological Surgical ward at CHH.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates must be enthusiastic &amp; self-motivated, and be committed to delivering a high quality service for patients to ensure accurate &amp; holistic assessment, ensuring &amp; enhancing the patients’ surgical journey. Previous experience within a surgical setting is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should have excellent communication skills and a desire to work within the multidisciplinary team delivering a co-ordinated approach to this group of patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IT skills and experience with electronic patient records is desirable, however training will be given.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicant must be able to exhibit their commitment to developing the service by demonstrating the ability to work independently as well as within a dedicated team to provide a high quality patient experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a supportive environment where you can develop both personally and professionally within an interesting and varied client group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Sister Kerry Wheeldon on ward 9 at CHH on telephone 01482 623009. Applications will be accepted electronically on-line.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
